This paper discusses the notion of fairness in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper explores the cultural and social context in which different fairness definitions have emerged, which could be categorized under "Computational Social Science" (cs.CY) or "Computational Economics" (cs.CE). The paper also discusses the mathematical methods for measuring fairness, which could be categorized under "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Finally, the paper touches on the ethical considerations of fairness, which could be categorized under "Emerging Technologies" (cs.ET).
